15.41	The_Blithedale_Romance	The Blithedale Romance	The Blithedale Romance (1852) is Nathaniel Hawthorne's third major romance. In Hawthorne (1879), Henry James called it "the lightest, the brightest, the liveliest" of Hawthorne's "unhumorous fictions."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6a/Blithedale_1st.jpg/200px-Blithedale_1st.jpg
